criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiologists GradeⅠ－II;

          -  Patients undergo low-risk elective surgery for benign diseases (including laparoscopic
             ovarian cyst removal, laparoscopic tubal ligation, laparoscopic tubal drainage, breast
             operation, thyroid operation, etc) ;

          -  Aged 18-45 years;

          -  Body Mass Index 18-25kg/m2, weight 40-65 kilograms;

          -  Agreed to participate in the research

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Difficult airway;

          -  upper respiratory tract infection within 2 weeks;

          -  history of allergy or long-term use of propofol and opioids;

          -  self-rating anxiety scale before operation indicates anxiety;

          -  pregnancy or lactation.
